FBIS4-36734 "drnes113_n_94001" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 LEBANON Abu-Nidal Group Member Claims Lockerbie Responsibility Abu-Nidal Group Member Claims Lockerbie Responsibility NC1306105594 Paris AFP in English 1048 GMT 13 Jun 94 NC1306105594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Beirut, June 13 (AFP) -- A member of Abu Nidal's radical Palestinian group Fatah Revolutionary Council claimed here on Monday responsibility for bombing a US airliner over Lockerbie, Scotland, in December 1988, which killed 270 people. Yusuf Sha'ban, 29, a suspect in the murder case of a Jordanian diplomat, told a Lebanese court he had placed the bomb that ripped through a Pan Am plane packed with Christmas travellers.
